Jacques Kallis (born 16 October 1975) is a former South African cricketer,
and, a former Test and ODI captain.
As a right-handed batsman and right-arm fast-medium swing bowler,
Kallis is regarded as one of the greatest cricketers of all time and one of the game's greatest all-rounders.
As of 2016 he was the only cricketer in the history of the game to score more than 10,000 runs
and take over 250 wickets in both ODI and Test match cricket, pouching 131 ODI catches along the way as well.
His Test match career in particular saw him score 13,289 runs, take 292 wickets and 200 catches respectively